04:32.520 --> 04:37.150
[♪♪♪]

04:41.580 --> 04:44.680
[CHILDREN LAUGH PLAYFULLY]

04:56.340 --> 04:58.133
[CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS]

04:59.720 --> 05:02.800
[WINDING FILM ADVANCE]

05:03.639 --> 05:05.724
[SHUTTER CLICKS]

05:06.930 --> 05:08.930
[ADVANCING FILM]

05:08.932 --> 05:11.350
[SUDDEN GUST OF WIND WHISTLING]

05:23.080 --> 05:24.117
[SHUTTER CLICKS]

05:26.880 --> 05:27.913
Hey.

05:30.970 --> 05:32.759
I didn't see you at breakfast.

05:32.760 --> 05:34.060
I ate in the barracks.

05:34.066 --> 05:35.669
It seemed easier.

05:35.670 --> 05:38.340
[WOMEN GIGGLING]

05:39.479 --> 05:41.529
Has it been any better?

05:41.530 --> 05:43.340
With the women in your barrack?

05:43.350 --> 05:44.840
It's the same.

05:44.850 --> 05:47.179
Awkward, but fine.

05:47.180 --> 05:49.799
Just like Catholic
school all over again,

05:49.800 --> 05:50.978
and I survived that.

05:54.920 --> 05:56.679
You don't have to do that.

05:56.680 --> 05:58.900
They don't have to do that.

06:00.720 --> 06:02.189
My shirt looks nice on you.

06:02.190 --> 06:03.819
[CHUCKLING]

06:03.820 --> 06:07.779
It doesn't, but... low on options.

06:07.780 --> 06:11.419
You can get some new
stuff when we go home.

06:11.420 --> 06:14.040
And when would that be?

06:14.050 --> 06:15.990
Two weeks.

06:15.999 --> 06:18.919
Or months.

06:18.920 --> 06:20.860
Tops.

06:22.170 --> 06:24.340
[CHILLING MUSIC SWELLS]

06:24.350 --> 06:26.972
[BACKGROUND CONVERSATIONS IN JAPANESE]

06:56.740 --> 06:58.599
Asako-san!

06:58.600 --> 07:01.050
Any word from Henry-san?

07:02.879 --> 07:06.659
I pray the spirits haven't taken them.

07:23.612 --> 07:25.322
That poor girl.

07:30.410 --> 07:31.840
But she did.

07:31.850 --> 07:33.705
Doesn't that say something?

07:54.440 --> 07:56.680
[CHILLING MUSIC SWELLS]

08:03.193 --> 08:06.195
[BIRDS SING]

08:06.196 --> 08:09.824
Those birds, are they swallows?

08:09.825 --> 08:12.359
I don't know the first
thing about birds.

08:12.360 --> 08:13.389
I'm not about to start

08:13.390 --> 08:15.163
when we're supposed to
be building a fence.

08:15.170 --> 08:17.219
[CHESTER]: Is that the big chief?

08:17.220 --> 08:18.249
Bowen?

08:18.250 --> 08:19.929
Major Bowen.

08:19.930 --> 08:21.169
[BOWEN]: ...the
difference is, mosquitoes

08:21.170 --> 08:22.619
stop sucking when you hit 'em.

08:22.620 --> 08:24.170
[CHUCKLING]

08:25.799 --> 08:27.843
You workin' hard, boys?

08:30.137 --> 08:31.799
What's your name, son?

08:31.800 --> 08:32.839
Chester.

08:32.840 --> 08:34.698
Chester Nakayama.

08:34.700 --> 08:35.850
Nakayama?

08:35.851 --> 08:38.389
I knew a Nakayama once...

08:38.390 --> 08:40.279
or was it Nakamura?

08:40.280 --> 08:42.938
Either way, he was a hell of a gardener.

08:42.940 --> 08:44.191
When will the fence be completed?

08:44.192 --> 08:46.569
- A month at the most, Major.
- Good.

08:46.570 --> 08:49.240
I don't need anybody going AWOL,

08:49.250 --> 08:51.999
so you boys better build
me a nice solid fence.

08:52.000 --> 08:54.244
You're supposed to be industrious.

09:00.660 --> 09:01.799
I guess it's no surprise

09:01.800 --> 09:03.640
that the guy who runs
this place is an asshole.

09:05.740 --> 09:07.889
How long have you been here?

09:07.890 --> 09:09.919
About a month. You?

09:09.920 --> 09:12.019
Got here last week from San Francisco,

09:12.020 --> 09:13.779
with my parents and my brother.

09:13.780 --> 09:15.439
Older sister's in Manzanar.

09:15.440 --> 09:16.839
Sounds terrible there.

09:16.840 --> 09:18.809
It's terrible here.

09:18.810 --> 09:20.311
Hey, where are you from?

09:20.312 --> 09:22.481
We're from Terminal Island.

09:26.000 --> 09:28.020
You can't miss what
you never had, right?

09:30.950 --> 09:32.079
Huh.

09:32.080 --> 09:34.519
I never thought I'd see that.

09:34.520 --> 09:36.569
What the hell...?

09:36.570 --> 09:38.399
[WALT]: Those guys are Nisei.

09:38.400 --> 09:40.959
[ALAN]: I heard that they're
recruiting overseas translators.

09:40.960 --> 09:42.540
[CHESTER]: That's rich.

09:42.542 --> 09:44.418
I thought we were
supposed to be the enemy.

09:44.419 --> 09:45.980
The test is tough.

09:45.984 --> 09:48.924
Even guys who have studied
in Japan don't pass.

09:51.900 --> 09:53.553
You're not considering it, are you?

09:54.250 --> 09:55.379
[SCOFFS]

09:55.380 --> 09:57.579
They put us here, and
expect us to sign up?

09:57.580 --> 09:58.600
Screw that.

10:00.320 --> 10:02.639
Good.

10:02.640 --> 10:05.019
[CRICKETS CHIRP]

10:05.020 --> 10:08.859
[DUKE ELLINGTON'S "ALL TOO SOON" PLAYS]

10:08.860 --> 10:13.073
[♪♪♪]

11:04.460 --> 11:06.450
[AMY WHISPERING] Asako-san! Asako-san!

11:08.620 --> 11:10.599
[WHISPERING] Henry-san, he's here!

11:10.600 --> 11:11.839
What?

11:11.840 --> 11:13.539
We were just dancing...

11:13.540 --> 11:15.593
He's here, at the camp.

11:15.594 --> 11:16.761
[GASPS]

11:28.520 --> 11:29.980
Henry-san.

12:14.060 --> 12:18.740
[BACKGROUND CONVERSATIONS]

12:22.827 --> 12:23.830
Chester.

12:25.664 --> 12:27.329
[GROWLING IN PROTEST]

12:27.330 --> 12:29.060
Let me.

12:33.171 --> 12:34.422
[SCREAMING IN PAIN]

12:49.688 --> 12:51.600
[GROANING IN PAIN]

12:56.600 --> 12:58.399
What the hell happened?

12:58.400 --> 12:59.820
Where were you?

12:59.823 --> 13:00.949
They didn't tell you?

13:03.243 --> 13:06.371
[BABY STARTS CRYING]

13:55.470 --> 14:00.925
[♪♪♪]

14:26.830 --> 14:30.600
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

16:14.860 --> 16:17.019
Morning, Pop.

16:17.020 --> 16:19.129
I brought you some breakfast.

16:22.280 --> 16:24.060
Luz.

16:27.020 --> 16:29.489
<i>Konnichiwa,</i> Nakayama-san.

16:29.490 --> 16:31.119
I've brought you some warm water

16:31.120 --> 16:33.399
to soak your hands and feet.

16:33.400 --> 16:35.640
It should help with the frostbite.

16:35.650 --> 16:38.060
Luz is studying to be a nurse.

16:39.501 --> 16:40.668
[PAN CLATTERING]

16:42.587 --> 16:45.215
- She's just trying to help!
- Chester, you should go.

16:50.358 --> 16:52.347
- [SETS PLATE DOWN]
- Luz...

17:04.260 --> 17:06.980
Hey, Chester, mind if I join?

17:10.720 --> 17:12.108
Ken Uehara.

17:12.109 --> 17:14.019
Oh, this is Amy.

17:14.020 --> 17:15.519
- Nice to meet...
- My sister,

17:15.520 --> 17:17.659
from Terminal Island?

17:17.660 --> 17:18.959
Have you ever been?

17:18.960 --> 17:21.260
No, but I hear it's nice.

17:21.270 --> 17:22.279
[THEY CHUCKLE SHYLY]

17:22.280 --> 17:24.419
- It's actually really nice.
- I imagine. I bet. Yeah.

17:24.420 --> 17:25.858
- [CHUCKLING]
- Where are you from?

17:25.859 --> 17:27.669
I'm from San Francisco.

17:27.670 --> 17:30.400
If somebody find love here,

17:30.410 --> 17:32.940
that be something.

17:34.847 --> 17:39.449
Pity about Yoshida-san.

17:39.450 --> 17:43.779
I never thought he snap.

17:43.780 --> 17:45.470
Guess you never know.

17:46.740 --> 17:49.139
I don't know.

17:49.140 --> 17:50.719
When it happened,

17:50.720 --> 17:52.739
Yoshida-san wasn't himself.

17:52.740 --> 17:57.600
You think... it was something else?

18:01.100 --> 18:03.159
<i>Bakemono?</i>

18:03.160 --> 18:04.909
<i>Yūrei?</i>

18:04.910 --> 18:07.919
I never used to believe in
that old country stuff.

18:07.920 --> 18:09.359
Old country?

18:09.360 --> 18:12.092
They in every country.

18:12.093 --> 18:14.887
<i>Yūrei</i> be anywhere you go.

18:17.030 --> 18:19.800
It follow you.

18:24.000 --> 18:26.020
[FURUYA BANGS OPEN THE DOOR]: Toshiro!

18:32.540 --> 18:33.690
[ROARING]

18:33.698 --> 18:35.658
- Toshiro!
- Tou-chan!

18:38.119 --> 18:39.620
[DISHES CLATTERING]

18:39.621 --> 18:41.121
- Toshiro!
- Tou-chan!

18:41.122 --> 18:43.124
Tou-chan, go back to bed!

18:48.620 --> 18:50.088
[WOMAN SCREAMING]

18:50.089 --> 18:51.548
[MAN]: Hey, stand back! Let me through!

18:51.549 --> 18:52.830
[CHOKING]

18:53.551 --> 18:55.928
[SCREAMING]

19:01.060 --> 19:02.289
Get him outta here!

19:02.290 --> 19:06.606
[RAGING AND SCREAMING]

19:08.691 --> 19:10.942
[SCREAMING AND RAGING]

19:10.943 --> 19:13.279
[CHILLING MUSIC SWELLS]

19:14.650 --> 19:17.460
[SCREAMING RECEDES]

19:20.880 --> 19:22.379
Let's just go.

19:22.380 --> 19:25.082
I can't be a secretary to these people.

19:25.083 --> 19:28.249
You need something to do.

19:28.250 --> 19:29.940
Sorry I kept you waiting.

19:29.950 --> 19:32.079
A man went crazy in the mess,

19:32.080 --> 19:34.160
a soldier took an unauthorized leak,

19:34.170 --> 19:36.301
and somebody destroyed a searchlight.

19:36.302 --> 19:39.554
Every goddamn day, it's somethin'.

19:39.555 --> 19:41.970
Come on in.

19:45.180 --> 19:46.229
Have a seat.

19:50.680 --> 19:53.777
So... how can I help?

19:53.778 --> 19:56.589
My name is Fumi Yoshida.

19:56.590 --> 19:58.359
My daughter, Amy,

19:58.360 --> 20:01.702
would like to offer her
secretarial services.

20:01.703 --> 20:03.454
Does she have any experience?

20:03.455 --> 20:06.240
She knows shorthand, and...

20:06.250 --> 20:08.119
How fast can you type?

20:08.120 --> 20:10.399
60 words per minute.

20:10.400 --> 20:12.059
But more than that,

20:12.060 --> 20:14.119
she would love to help her country

20:14.120 --> 20:16.175
during a time of war.

20:17.320 --> 20:18.720
Wouldn't you, Amy?

20:23.220 --> 20:24.679
So much paperwork.

20:24.680 --> 20:27.340
I could certainly use a new secretary.

20:27.350 --> 20:31.480
Especially one as patriotic
as your daughter.

20:35.770 --> 20:39.920
[♪♪♪]

21:02.260 --> 21:05.080
[QUIETLY]: Furuya-san...

21:05.920 --> 21:07.810
Furuya-san...

21:09.900 --> 21:11.340
Furuya-san...

21:11.350 --> 21:12.640
it's Chester.

21:12.650 --> 21:15.879
I brought you some saké. Homemade.

21:15.880 --> 21:17.519
Where is Toshiro?

21:17.520 --> 21:18.569
Is he okay?

21:18.570 --> 21:19.979
He's with my mother.

21:19.980 --> 21:21.115
She's taking care of him.

21:25.160 --> 21:26.719
What happened today?

21:26.720 --> 21:27.747
Why did you attack him?

21:27.748 --> 21:29.707
I didn't! It wasn't me!

21:30.520 --> 21:32.290
Tell him.

21:32.293 --> 21:33.753
Tell him it wasn't me.

21:35.320 --> 21:37.299
Then what was it?

21:37.300 --> 21:41.460
Do you remember saying
something about swallows?

21:42.920 --> 21:46.300
I felt... something inside of me.

21:49.769 --> 21:51.437
Haunting you?

21:52.500 --> 21:54.390
Has this happened to you?

21:56.660 --> 22:00.399
No... but I've seen it.

22:00.400 --> 22:03.530
It doesn't stop.

22:03.533 --> 22:07.560
It's with me wherever I go.

22:07.566 --> 22:09.129
[VOICES APPROACH]

22:09.130 --> 22:10.779
You're gonna be next.

22:10.780 --> 22:12.299
It's that <i>hakujin</i> MP.

22:12.300 --> 22:13.333
Get out of here,

22:13.334 --> 22:14.836
or they'll put you in with me.

22:18.060 --> 22:20.880
[YOSHIDA'S VOICE]:
Chester, you have to go.

22:20.883 --> 22:23.343
Chester! You have to go!

22:23.344 --> 22:26.013
[CHILLING MUSIC SWELLS]

22:35.300 --> 22:36.849
[WALT]: Sorry, but I don't buy it.

22:36.850 --> 22:39.179
You got a lot more
marbles than Furuya-san.

22:39.180 --> 22:41.589
He said he felt like
he was being watched,

22:41.590 --> 22:44.399
- and now...
- Yeah, he... he cracked up.

22:44.400 --> 22:46.329
Like...

22:46.330 --> 22:48.819
Well, like my dad.

22:48.820 --> 22:50.360
Hey, that day,

22:50.370 --> 22:52.260
when he came running to us,

22:52.270 --> 22:55.589
he said, "You have to go."

22:55.590 --> 22:57.999
Was that to both of us?

22:58.000 --> 23:01.609
No, it was... it was just you.

23:01.610 --> 23:03.079
"Chester, you have to go."

23:03.080 --> 23:04.780
But why would he say that?

23:04.782 --> 23:06.178
I've given up wondering.

23:07.559 --> 23:09.119
She's not in there.

23:09.120 --> 23:10.180
Do you know where she is?

23:10.190 --> 23:12.435
I think she went to the infirmary.

23:14.600 --> 23:15.760
I don't need a band-aid!

23:15.770 --> 23:18.689
I need you to make sure my baby is okay!

23:18.690 --> 23:20.899
Luz, are you okay?

23:20.900 --> 23:23.439
I fell. I'm fine.

23:23.440 --> 23:25.159
I want this doctor to check the baby,

23:25.160 --> 23:28.780
but all he's done is given me
a stupid band-aid for my arm.

23:44.050 --> 23:46.200
He needs you to lie down.

23:55.470 --> 23:56.520
Please be okay.

24:05.320 --> 24:06.720
Hmm.

24:13.300 --> 24:14.319
The baby is fine.

24:14.320 --> 24:16.706
Yeah. I just felt a kick.

24:16.707 --> 24:18.750
Oh, my God...

24:21.600 --> 24:23.919
[CHESTER]: How did this happen?

24:23.920 --> 24:25.679
It was stupid.

24:25.680 --> 24:28.799
I... I was walking out
to use the latrine,

24:28.800 --> 24:31.260
and, you know, with the
wind and the rain,

24:31.270 --> 24:33.040
I lost my footing on the steps.

24:33.050 --> 24:34.999
Because of the wind?

24:35.000 --> 24:37.099
You just fell?

24:37.100 --> 24:38.646
I told you it was stupid.

24:41.780 --> 24:43.600
You're sure it was an accident?

24:43.609 --> 24:45.740
Of course.

24:45.741 --> 24:48.029
What else could it be?

24:48.030 --> 24:52.409
[♪♪♪]

25:01.820 --> 25:05.630
[CHILLING MUSIC SWELLS]

25:05.631 --> 25:08.980
[KEYS RATTLE]

25:08.981 --> 25:10.428
Who's that?

25:13.431 --> 25:15.510
What are you doing?

25:18.060 --> 25:20.770
Where are you taking me?

25:20.771 --> 25:22.980
Please!

25:24.800 --> 25:26.109
Please,

25:26.110 --> 25:28.860
I've done nothing.

25:36.900 --> 25:39.200
[FOOTSTEPS RECEDE]

25:43.627 --> 25:44.754
Help!

25:51.260 --> 25:52.650
[RUSTLING]

25:55.586 --> 25:56.760
[TWIG SNAP]

26:00.400 --> 26:04.159
[GASPING]

26:04.160 --> 26:06.180
[SOBBING]

27:03.020 --> 27:06.020
[FURUYA GROANS IN PAIN]

27:06.060 --> 27:09.250
[FLESH RENDING]

27:15.219 --> 27:16.929
[GURGLING]

27:23.170 --> 27:24.228
[SPLUTTERS WEAKLY]

27:45.830 --> 27:48.760
Go, go, go! Come on!

27:48.770 --> 27:50.879
- How did he miss that?
- [APPLAUSE]

27:50.880 --> 27:52.260
Here you go.

27:52.270 --> 27:55.100
- Come on.
- Come on, you can do this.

27:56.420 --> 27:57.420
- [BAT HITS BALL]
- Yeah!

27:57.421 --> 27:59.550
- Catch it, catch it!
- [APPLAUSE]

28:15.480 --> 28:19.100
[SCREAMING IN TERROR]

28:25.760 --> 28:26.999
He was found in the woods.

28:27.000 --> 28:28.719
It doesn't make any sense.

28:28.720 --> 28:29.839
But if it was suicide,

28:29.840 --> 28:31.979
why not just kill
yourself in the stockade?

28:31.980 --> 28:33.659
Maybe it wasn't.

28:33.660 --> 28:35.439
I heard that the kid who found the body

28:35.440 --> 28:36.949
saw a woman in the woods.

28:36.950 --> 28:38.939
- What kind of woman?
- In a kimono.

28:38.940 --> 28:40.260
Like Meiji times or something.

28:40.270 --> 28:42.049
That kid didn't see shit.

28:42.050 --> 28:44.060
Our own army, they're killing us,

28:44.070 --> 28:45.779
one by one.

28:45.780 --> 28:47.450
Weird way for them to do it.

28:47.458 --> 28:49.938
Hey, Walt, the other
day, when Luz fell...

28:49.939 --> 28:51.999
Yeah, it was an accident.

28:52.000 --> 28:53.560
What if it wasn't?

28:53.567 --> 28:55.879
I can't stop thinking about
what your dad said to me

28:55.880 --> 28:56.899
at the race track.

28:56.900 --> 28:58.979
- That again?
- And your mom?

28:58.980 --> 29:02.160
She said there's evil around me.

29:02.170 --> 29:03.840
- What if she's right?
- So what,

29:03.850 --> 29:06.400
you really think if you
go, it'll follow you?

29:09.880 --> 29:12.370
Good luck trying to leave this place.

29:15.172 --> 29:17.883
Have you done any
translation work before,

29:17.884 --> 29:21.419
or gone to Japanese language school?

29:21.420 --> 29:23.429
Mostly I just speak some at home.

29:23.430 --> 29:25.766
Let's start with the
military translation.

29:28.220 --> 29:30.439
[EXHALES]

29:30.440 --> 29:33.139
Okay, so this is a step-by-step guide

29:33.140 --> 29:34.599
to using a rifle.

29:34.600 --> 29:36.540
An Arisaka type,

29:36.550 --> 29:38.862
or a Yuhan, maybe?

29:41.080 --> 29:43.540
Uh...

29:43.550 --> 29:47.319
It says to "manually adjust...

29:47.320 --> 29:50.879
the seeing... device..."

29:50.880 --> 29:53.499
Oh, the sight, I guess.

29:53.500 --> 29:55.959
Uh, "from a five...

29:55.960 --> 29:58.549
to a 2.5..."

30:01.940 --> 30:03.289
I'm sorry, there are a
lot of weaponry terms

30:03.290 --> 30:04.305
I'm unfamiliar with.

30:06.880 --> 30:08.579
Look at this.

30:08.580 --> 30:09.727
We found it on a soldier.

30:15.160 --> 30:17.349
"Dearest Toshiko,"

30:17.350 --> 30:19.059
Nee-you...

30:19.060 --> 30:21.447
Oh, it's... "we made it to New Guinea."

30:22.280 --> 30:23.690
Then, "Thick...

30:23.699 --> 30:26.576
the air is thick...

30:26.577 --> 30:28.619
Not like Osaka...

30:28.620 --> 30:32.439
cherry blossoms fall.

30:32.440 --> 30:35.293
An orchid..."

30:35.294 --> 30:36.919
This is a poem,

30:36.920 --> 30:39.419
inside the letter.

30:39.420 --> 30:42.460
Um, "the window..."

30:42.470 --> 30:43.885
Um...

30:43.886 --> 30:47.930
"where I was born," maybe?

30:47.931 --> 30:50.079
"I will be dreaming...

30:50.080 --> 30:52.310
of it tomorrow.

30:52.311 --> 30:56.860
I hope to be home for the next bloom."

30:58.760 --> 31:00.110
Anything else?

31:01.580 --> 31:03.610
That's all that it says.

31:03.614 --> 31:04.907
I appreciate you coming in.

31:05.540 --> 31:07.360
Sir!

31:08.060 --> 31:09.780
Please.

31:09.787 --> 31:11.909
I have people depending on me.

31:11.910 --> 31:14.260
In order to help them, I
have to get out of here.

31:14.270 --> 31:16.299
I appreciate that, but I need people

31:16.300 --> 31:17.669
who can translate letters like this

31:17.670 --> 31:20.139
with ease.

31:20.140 --> 31:22.260
Translate?

31:22.262 --> 31:23.549
Or break the code?

31:23.550 --> 31:25.427
What code?

31:26.460 --> 31:28.340
The weird <i> tanka</i>,

31:28.350 --> 31:30.360
the one I could barely translate.

31:30.370 --> 31:31.891
The language is...

31:31.892 --> 31:33.639
What's a <i> tanka</i> ?

31:33.640 --> 31:35.890
A five-line poem.

31:35.896 --> 31:38.700
5-7-5-7-7.

31:38.703 --> 31:40.870
31 beats.

31:40.872 --> 31:42.486
My mom used to read books of them.

31:44.109 --> 31:46.189
What's strange about this poem?

31:46.190 --> 31:50.299
The wording is unusual,

31:50.300 --> 31:52.999
and not just because it's poetry.

31:53.000 --> 31:55.279
Uh...

31:55.280 --> 31:57.539
The author switched things around

31:57.540 --> 32:01.079
so that the first syllable of each line,

32:01.080 --> 32:03.459
when you say it together in a row,

32:03.460 --> 32:05.170
spells something out,

32:05.175 --> 32:07.803
"Sa-ra-ma-u-a."

32:09.700 --> 32:11.720
That's Salamaua, isn't it?

32:12.580 --> 32:15.390
That spot in New Guinea,
from the news a while back?

32:17.300 --> 32:19.850
But I'm guessing you knew that already.

32:21.246 --> 32:22.692
Just curious,

32:22.693 --> 32:25.729
how many other guys saw it?

32:29.880 --> 32:31.610
You're joining the Army?

32:32.720 --> 32:35.619
It's an opportunity to earn a real wage.

32:35.620 --> 32:39.079
More than I've made... ever.

32:39.080 --> 32:40.979
It says you're shipping out in two days.

32:40.980 --> 32:43.299
That can't be right.

32:43.300 --> 32:45.510
Where are they even sending you,

32:45.512 --> 32:47.269
and for how long?

32:47.270 --> 32:50.939
I'll start in Minnesota, for training,

32:50.940 --> 32:54.339
then... wherever I'm needed,

32:54.340 --> 32:56.185
but I'll send all the money home.

32:57.320 --> 32:59.230
Home?

33:00.780 --> 33:02.140
What home?

33:03.580 --> 33:05.499
I know it's a shock.

33:05.500 --> 33:07.112
I do.

33:08.160 --> 33:09.940
You're running away.

33:13.300 --> 33:15.409
My parents, they...
they'll take care of you...

33:15.410 --> 33:16.496
I don't want them to take care of me.

33:16.497 --> 33:17.955
I need to know that you'll be okay.

33:17.956 --> 33:19.625
Then stay!

33:24.970 --> 33:27.240
There has to be another way.

33:27.250 --> 33:28.674
Other people here are managing.

33:28.675 --> 33:30.636
I'm not like other people.

33:33.260 --> 33:34.549
[SIGHS]

33:34.550 --> 33:37.399
Isn't this what you want from me?

33:37.400 --> 33:39.699
To have a plan?

33:39.700 --> 33:41.062
That's what I'm doing.

33:41.063 --> 33:43.565
That's what this is.

33:46.040 --> 33:49.729
I swear to you, all of this...

33:49.730 --> 33:53.260
it's for you

33:53.270 --> 33:55.490
and the baby.

34:01.060 --> 34:03.210
What if you don't come back?

34:06.420 --> 34:08.830
I'm a translator.

34:08.837 --> 34:12.050
I won't see any combat.

34:17.090 --> 34:21.600
[JAZZ RECORD PLAYS IN THE DISTANCE]

34:24.540 --> 34:27.520
It's nice,

34:27.525 --> 34:29.570
the music.

34:32.120 --> 34:35.320
If I close my eyes,

34:35.330 --> 34:39.705
I can maybe forget where we are.

34:40.980 --> 34:44.498
Maybe.

34:44.500 --> 34:48.230
You know...

34:48.234 --> 34:51.969
we've never danced together...

34:54.960 --> 34:57.930
and if you're leaving...

34:59.429 --> 35:00.934
We should rectify that.

35:05.160 --> 35:09.220
[♪♪♪]

35:47.560 --> 35:49.980
[DOOR OPENING]

35:51.880 --> 35:53.400
[DOOR CLOSING]

35:55.151 --> 35:58.620
I see you found the saké.

36:00.450 --> 36:04.740
So Mom told you I'm leaving?

36:04.750 --> 36:05.999
I'm going to be a translator

36:06.000 --> 36:08.540
in a new military intelligence service,

36:08.550 --> 36:11.540
with other Nisei.

36:11.550 --> 36:14.599
So what's keeping you?

36:14.600 --> 36:16.640
Go.

36:21.720 --> 36:24.179
Luz is going to move in here, Pop,

36:24.180 --> 36:27.060
and you...

36:31.600 --> 36:34.359
I know you've been through a lot.

36:34.360 --> 36:36.519
I do,

36:36.520 --> 36:39.379
but Mom can't do everything.

36:39.380 --> 36:40.719
I need you to get out of bed

36:40.720 --> 36:43.079
and take care of this family,

36:43.080 --> 36:45.399
and that includes Luz.

36:45.400 --> 36:48.339
I sacrifice so much for you,

36:48.340 --> 36:51.799
and this is how you repay it?

36:51.800 --> 36:53.399
By leaving your family

36:53.400 --> 36:56.860
so you can run off and be a spy?

36:58.980 --> 37:01.579
You told me to enlist.

37:01.580 --> 37:06.579
That was before I knew
what they were capable of.

37:06.580 --> 37:08.540
Roosevelt.

37:08.550 --> 37:11.319
The government.

37:11.320 --> 37:13.560
They see us as rats.

37:14.760 --> 37:15.959
Once we win the war,

37:15.960 --> 37:18.113
they won't look at us like that again.

37:19.080 --> 37:22.499
I used to think like that.

37:22.500 --> 37:25.419
You treat people good,

37:25.420 --> 37:28.539
they see the good in you,

37:28.540 --> 37:32.359
the truth...

37:32.360 --> 37:36.600
but you get old, and you learn...

37:36.603 --> 37:38.959
they don't.

37:38.960 --> 37:40.979
They beat me.

37:40.980 --> 37:44.089
They left me in the cold,

37:44.090 --> 37:47.040
and now you join them.

37:49.420 --> 37:51.769
But they sent you back here.

37:51.770 --> 37:55.740
You're here now, with Ma.

37:55.750 --> 37:57.740
You have a grandbaby on the way,

37:57.750 --> 37:59.859
and yet...

37:59.860 --> 38:02.190
you just sit here.

38:02.199 --> 38:03.741
That's no way to live.

38:03.742 --> 38:06.199
It's not,

38:06.200 --> 38:09.260
but this is what we do.

38:09.270 --> 38:11.460
<i>Gaman.</i>

38:12.320 --> 38:15.199
But you...

38:15.200 --> 38:17.005
you run away.

38:22.860 --> 38:25.499
Go.

38:25.500 --> 38:28.999
If you have to go, Chester,

38:29.000 --> 38:31.340
you have to go.

38:35.480 --> 38:39.060
At least I'm doing something.

38:41.680 --> 38:44.819
[DOOR OPENS]

38:44.820 --> 38:46.993
[WALT]: How much did you tell Luz?

38:46.994 --> 38:49.819
Just that it's a good job.

38:49.820 --> 38:53.120
She's worried enough as it is.

38:59.714 --> 39:01.300
Take care.

39:06.400 --> 39:09.010
That Ken guy, he being nice to you?

39:18.380 --> 39:21.570
You're going to look so
handsome in uniform.

39:23.267 --> 39:24.531
We'll see after Luz.

39:25.824 --> 39:28.785
Pop will come around.

39:37.002 --> 39:40.088
I found a woman who
was making dresses...

39:40.100 --> 39:42.939
in case you get sick
of wearing my shirts.

39:42.940 --> 39:45.594
[CHUCKLES]

39:50.260 --> 39:52.720
[LAUGHING]

39:55.540 --> 39:57.919
How did you pay for it?

39:57.920 --> 40:00.691
I... traded my camera for it.

40:00.692 --> 40:03.530
Chester...

40:05.780 --> 40:07.240
Write as soon as you can.

40:09.722 --> 40:11.700
[WIND GUSTS SUDDENLY]

40:24.380 --> 40:26.460
Chester!

40:45.980 --> 40:47.819
What's she doing?

40:47.820 --> 40:49.679
If Chester dies and there's no body,

40:49.680 --> 40:51.479
she can cremate the hair.

40:51.480 --> 40:53.740
Give him a proper burial.

40:56.140 --> 40:59.600
[ENGINES STARTING]

41:29.660 --> 41:31.070
Asako-san!

41:32.575 --> 41:35.327
Do you know if there's
another doctor at the camp?

41:35.328 --> 41:37.038
Why? What's wrong?

41:41.390 --> 41:43.080
I feel fine,

41:43.090 --> 41:46.256
but I don't want to see
Dr. Kitamura again.

41:47.960 --> 41:51.599
A woman in the <i> mesu</i>
told me about a midwife,

41:51.600 --> 41:54.619
in the new barracks, north
of the guard tower.

41:54.620 --> 41:56.057
Why don't I come with you?

41:56.058 --> 41:57.779
I can make it.

41:57.780 --> 41:59.210
<i>Arigato.</i>

42:03.340 --> 42:08.902
[WOMAN SINGING SOFTLY]

42:08.903 --> 42:12.450
[SINGING SOFTLY]

42:25.180 --> 42:26.609
I'm sorry,

42:26.610 --> 42:28.640
I don't understand.

42:28.650 --> 42:32.319
Can you tell me if the head...

42:32.320 --> 42:33.940
Is it down?

42:33.950 --> 42:36.555
- The head... down?
- [MURMURS GENTLY]

42:39.540 --> 42:40.679
Up?

42:40.680 --> 42:43.799
[SIGHS] Okay.

42:43.800 --> 42:46.220
Okay, that's a relief.

42:49.220 --> 42:55.820
[SINGING SOFTLY]

